### Warnings
**1. String interpolation bug in `pruneDanglingImages` â€” filter argument is malformed**
**File:** `koncerto-deploy/src/main/kotlin/com/flexsentlabs/koncerto/deploy/DockerLaunchCleaner.kt`
```kotlin
// Line ~130:
runDocker("image", "prune", "-f", "--filter", "label=$DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_LABEL=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_VALUE}")
```
`$DockerEntityPolicy` expands to `DockerEntityPolicy.toString()` (the object's default string representation), so Docker receives a filter like `label=com.flexsentlabs.koncerto.deploy.DockerEntityPolicy@abc123.MANAGED_LABEL=koncerto`. The managed-label-selective first pass is a no-op; the fallback `image prune -f` runs unconditionally and prunes all dangling layers including any non-managed ones. Intent is not preserved.
Fix: `"label=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_LABEL}=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_VALUE}"`
